 submission and necessary follow-up. Nurture relationships with funders through meetings, presentations, regular communications, and/or arranging for meetings with HHF's management and/or programmatic staff. Coordinate the gathering of information (budgets, materials, evaluation reports, etc.) to support grant requests and reporting. Track the fulfillment of grants with program and finance staff and serve as an ongoing liaison to donors. Individual Gifts Work with Executive and Board to identify, cultivate, and solicit major gift prospects and donors. Serve as primary point person working with direct mail vendor on appeals, which includes leveraging existing data to build our donor base. Conduct donor profiles to determine who has the interest / capacity /propensity to give. Implement donor cultivation and fundraising events to support development goals. Responsible for developing donor communications and materials, including but not limited to, special letters, gift acknowledgments, proposals, newsletters, e-appeals and packages for fundraising. Corporate Support Expand and implement HHF's current corporate partnership program. Ensure new corporate opportunities are in alignment with HHF brand. Develop creative packages to secure funding from corporations and proactively manage the execution of those deliverables with corporate partners and HHF's staff. Donor Communications/Outreach Develop written communications to donors and prospects through print and online media including: Fund-raising publications, communications materials, such as press releases, e-appeals, cultivation, solicitation and acknowledgment letters. Work with the Program and Communication Manager to ensure all communications are aligned with development goals and objectives. The position is with HHF, a non-profit scientific research organization, headquartered in midtown Manhattan. While this position is open to everyone, candidates should preferably be in mid-career and interested in an evolving role with potential for leadership responsibilities. It is a full-time position with excellent benefits. Required Qualifications: Bachelor's Degree required, Advance Degree preferred. Minimum of ten years of experience in development or senior client relationship roles. Demonstrated success in securing major support (five and six figure gifts) from private sources. Mission-minded with a strong interest in research and education. Ability to work as a member of a team and develop effective working relationships with all. Commitment to professional ethics in working with highly confidential, sensitive information. Detail oriented and organized, with the strong ability to successfully multi-task Experience with the use of social media for marketing or fundraising campaigns. Excellent verbal and written communication skills. Proven ability to make decisions and solve problems independently, effectively, and creatively. Extensive computer skills, including intermediate or higher level proficiency with Microsoft Office (EXCEL, PowerPoint, and Word) and experience working with electronic donor tracking systems/databases (Raiser's Edge preferred). Some evening, weekend, and travel required. Sense of humor preferred More / Less How to apply If interested: Please e-mail your resume, cover letter and salary requirements to careers@hhf.org . Only people selected for interviews will be contacted. Inquiries from direct applicants only preferred - no recruiters or phone calls please. Please note: HHF is a non-profit, public benefit 501c(3) corporation and operates as an equal opportunity employer. This job description is general in nature and is not designed to contain or to be interpreted as a comprehensive inventory of all duties, responsibilities and qualifications of the position. More / Less Location 363 Seventh Avenue, 10th Floor, New York, NY, 10001, US More / Less Details Education requirements 4-year degree Employment type Full time Professional level None specified Job fu