form and/or are responsive to program and policy directions and recommendations. • Stay abreast of latest research developments in maternal health. • Oversee administrative aspects of SMM and MM surveillance. • Establish and maintain strong connection with CDC to ensure alignment in SMM algorithm and other aspects of the work. • Hire and manage interns or consultants to assist with analysis, chart abstractions, and data documentation. • Participate in Maternal Mortality Review Committee. • Liaise with the Division of Epidemiology and Office of Vital Statistics regarding data analysis needs and collaborative efforts. • Other duties as assigned. Minimum Qual Requirements: 1. A doctorate degree from an accredited college or university with specialization in an appropriate field of physical, biological, environmental or social science and one year of full-time experience in a responsible supervisory, administrative or research capacity in the appropriate field of specialization; or 2. A master's degree from an accredited college or university with specialization in an appropriate field of physical, biological, environmental or social science and three years of responsible full-time research experience in the appropriate field of specialization. Preferred Skills: • Graduate degree in public health, PhD preferred •  Minimum of five years of experience with surveillance research and data analysis using advanced statistical software (SAS, STATA, and preferable SQL) • Experience with large administrative datasets and clinical coding structures • Extensive experience in conducting public health surveillance • Strong quantitative research methods and analysis skills • Strong writing skills with a track record in publications • Exceptional interpersonal and teamwork skills • Proven coordination and organizational skills • Excellent communication skills] •  Deep knowledge of the science of maternal and infant health outcomes within the domestic setting, with knowledge of disparities in health outcomes. More / Less How to apply Apply online with a cover letter to https://a127-jobs.nyc.gov/ .  In the Job ID search bar, enter: job ID  # 234433. More / Less Location 42-09 28th Street, Long Island City, NY, 11101, US More / Less Details Education requirements Master's degree , MPH , Biology , Statistics , Epidemiology Employment type Full time Professional level Professional Salary details $ 76,340.00 - $100,322.00 Job function MPH , Research Owner's areas of focus Health and medicine , Mental health , Government oversight and reform More / Less Map More / Less Get career tips from our experts Half the Sky Appears: A Double-Book Review posted 3 days ago 3 Ways to Bring Joy to Your Job Search posted 6 days ago Should I Resend my Re-done Resume? posted 17 days ago 5 Entrepreneurial Techniques to Drive Your Nonprofit Career posted 20 days ago Without Fail: How Learning From Mistakes Leads to Success posted 24 days ago About History Our Team Working Here Learn Nonprofit Careers Volunteering Volunteering Abroad Grad School Attend Idealist Grad Fairs linkedin twitter facebook youtube Terms and Conditions | Privacy Policy | Community Guidelines © 1995- 2016 , Action Without Borders Idealist.org by Idealist.org is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivs 3.0 Unported License . Based on a work at www.idealist.org . Permissions beyond the scope of this license may be available at http://www.idealist.org . close Email Facebook Twitter Social Sharing by Janrain Share with Your Friends By Email Email sent Thanks for sharing with your contacts via email. Share with your other networks too! Start Over Select your contacts x + 11 Edit Done Close Done Selected contacts x + 11 Edit Done Close Done x + 30 Edit Done or browse contacts and 0 more x + It appears the URL has been modified. Restore? -84 Edit Done x + -155 Edit Done Job (Long Island City): Sr. Research Analyst, Surveillance, Maternal, - idealist.org http://www.idealist.org/s